text.tspan: Sample sizes adjusted for clustering using an ICC of 0.02 (author’s do not mention any assumptions for ICC. An ICC of 0.02 is usually used for school-based interventions). Design effect applied to account for 2 classes (clusters).
Tau² calculated by DerSimonian and Laird method.
(C) Blinding of participants and personnel (performance bias): cognitive function/motor skill development
(D) Blinding of outcome assessment (detection bias): cognitive function/motor skill development
(E) Incomplete outcome data (attrition bias): cognitive function/motor skill development
